data.description: Close to the Loop 303 and US60, Corte Bella Community is a gated community for active adults 45 and older. This Alameda model with Casita is nestled in a tranquil cul-de-sac with north-south exposure, and is the largest lot in the subdivision, giving an enhanced sense of privacy. The Casita is complete with its own private entrance and a fully equipped kitchen, a rare find within the subdivision. The main kitchen boasts 42'' cherry cabinets adorned with braid trim, glass fronts and under-cabinet lighting, as well as thick slab granite countertops and backsplash, stainless-steel appliances, 5-burner gas range, and a garbage compacter. You will also appreciate the custom drapes and blinds, in addition to blackout shades in the living areas, helping to cut down on electricity costs.  The laundry room is spacious complete with cabinets, sink and a fold-out ironing board. This residence has been meticulously maintained, including a  HVAC system that was serviced annually (see Documents tab) and the home has had several updates since 2019. An added bonus, there's an opportunity to purchase the furniture along with this exceptional home.
